The Prison Service has said 256 places at HMP Featherstone, near Wolverhampton will be changed. The category C spaces will make way for category A spaces which are also being discussed. Most staff will be shifted out when they first start working at these two sites at the end of the current year. A further three-year extension of their workforce from April, 2016, will see them at Wolverhampton to provide accommodation for up for 24 months each.

HMP St Stephen's Park has been moved to the other side of the ground due to concerns about an increase in gang violence. Work is being done at the centre but staff from the South West Centre will make up the rest. As of today, it has worked just six shifts in nine years.
]A group of volunteers are now at work to find accommodation, meals but no further services have been provided at the sites. The C-space is a part of a comprehensive scheme that was designed to offer job training and support
